== INITIAL CODEBASE STATE (pre-implementation) ==

The codebase already had the following infrastructure in place:
- TaskInput enum with ChatFirst { prompt }, ChatFollowup { message }, Loop, Inbox variants
- Server routes: POST /sessions, POST /sessions/:id/input, POST /workers/tasks/pull, POST /workers/tasks/:id/complete
- Worker task executor pipeline: clone -> branch -> run agent -> commit -> push -> complete
- Agent executor with stream-json parsing and assistant_reply extraction
- Session/job state machine with transitions
- History assembly inline in send_input route
- Database schema with jobs.task_input (JSONB), jobs.assistant_reply columns

== CHANGES MADE ==

### 1. api-types/src/workers.rs - Expanded TaskInput::ChatFollowup
Before:
```rust
ChatFollowup {
    message: String,
},
```
After:
```rust
ChatFollowup {
    session_prompt: String,
    message: String,
    #[serde(default)]
    history: Vec<String>,
    #[serde(default)]
    history_assistant: Vec<String>,
    #[serde(default)]
    history_truncated: bool,
},
```
This makes the worker receive the full chat context (session_prompt, history, history_assistant, history_truncated) when processing a followup job, instead of just the message.

### 2. worker/src/task_executor.rs - Multi-turn prompt construction
Added `build_chat_followup_prompt()` function that constructs a combined prompt:
```
Original goal: {session_prompt}

Conversation history:
User: {history[0]}
Assistant: {history_assistant[0]}
...

User: {message}
```

Updated the prompt extraction match arm for ChatFollowup to use this function instead of just returning `message`.

Also added 4 unit tests:
- test_build_chat_followup_prompt_basic
- test_build_chat_followup_prompt_truncated
- test_build_chat_followup_prompt_no_history
- test_chat_followup_prompt_extraction

### 3. server/src/engine/chat.rs - NEW MODULE
Created `engine/chat.rs` with:
- `ChatHistory` struct: session_prompt, user_messages, assistant_replies, truncated
- `assemble_history()`: queries completed jobs, extracts user messages and assistant replies, applies cap (max_turns), sets truncated flag
- `update_chat_session_status()`: chat sessions stay "running" after job completion to allow follow-up input (never auto-complete)

### 4. server/src/engine/mod.rs - Chat-specific job completion handling
Updated `on_job_completed()` to handle chat workflow specially:
- Chat sessions call `chat::update_chat_session_status()` instead of the generic `update_session_status()`
- This keeps the session in "running" state after job completion

### 5. server/src/routes/sessions.rs - Refactored send_input
Replaced the inline history assembly logic in `send_input()` with a call to `engine::chat::assemble_history()`. The JSON structure is the same but the code is cleaner and reusable.

### 6. server/tests/tasks_test.rs - Fixed existing test
Updated `test_session_status_updates_after_completion` to expect "running" instead of "completed" for chat sessions.

